<article>
    <h1>The Re-Align Frame&#xAD;work</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201104/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-04"><time>2020-11-04</time></a>
        - <span>THE BIG STORY</span>
        - <span role="byline">MIN&#xAD;ISTRY OF LAW STRAITS TIMES GRAPH&#xAD;ICS</span>
    </section>

    <p>Small and mi­cro busi­nesses</p>
    <p>They must meet two key cri­te­ria, which will be spec­i­fied in sub­sidiary leg­is­la­tion:</p>
    <p>An­nual rev­enue cap</p>
    <p>Sig­nif­i­cant fall in rev­enue due to Covid-19</p>
    <p>What con­tracts are cov­ered?</p>
    <p>• Must be gov­erned by Sin­ga­pore law</p>
    <p>• En­tered into be­fore March 25</p>
    <p>• At least one party must have a place of busi­ness in Sin­ga­pore</p>
    <p>• In­cludes con­tracts with the Gov­ern­ment</p>
    <p>• Types of con­tracts:</p>
    <p>- Leases or li­cences for com­mer­cial prop­erty</p>
    <p>- Con­tracts for the sale and pur­chase of goods and ser­vices</p>
    <p>Rental agree­ments for com­mer­cial equip­ment and ve­hi­cles</p>
    <p>Hire-pur­chase or con­di­tional sales agree­ments for com­mer­cial equip­ment and ve­hi­cles</p>
    <p>What con­tracts are not cov­ered?</p>
    <p>• Long-term leases of more than five years</p>
    <p>• Con­sumer con­tracts</p>
    <p>• Em­ploy­ment con­tracts</p>
    <p>• Fi­nan­cial and in­sur­ance con­tracts</p>
    <p>• Con­struc­tion and sup­ply con­tracts</p>
    <p>• Con­tracts im­pact­ing na­tional in­ter­est and es­sen­tial ser­vices (Note: These con­tracts may be rene­go­ti­ated but not ter­mi­nated)</p>
    <p>• Com­mod­ity con­tracts</p>
    <p>• Con­tracts where the ap­pli­ca­tion of the frame­work is in­con­sis­tent with Sin­ga­pore’s in­ter­na­tional obli­ga­tions</p>
    <p>Source:</p>


